========================================
DEVIATION: redsocks config permission bug
========================================

BUG: proxy_manager.py writes /run/openauto/redsocks.conf as root with 0600
then starts redsocks via 'sudo -u redsocks redsocks -c ...' which cannot
read the file (Permission denied). The proxy_manager-spawned redsocks fails
silently, and the system redsocks.service (using /etc/redsocks.conf pointing
to 127.0.0.1:1080) is what's actually listening on 12345.

WORKAROUND for validation: Stop system redsocks, write correct config with
appropriate permissions, start redsocks manually as redsocks user.

ROOT CAUSE FIX NEEDED: proxy_manager.py should use 0o640 permissions and
chown to root:redsocks (or use the redsocks group) so the redsocks user
can read the config file.

